Dasysyrphus hilaris is a Palearctic hoverfly.
It is a member of a cryptic species complex which includes
Dasysyrphus venustus the most frequent and widely distributed species
of the genus. Dasysyrphus hilaris is known with a level of certainty only from Ireland, Great Britain, Norway, France (Vosges, Alps, Pyrenees) and Liechtenstein.This species cannot be determined using existing keys.